English definition/description:
Increased frequency in passing of urine. If often occurs when 1) kidney yang fails to perform qi transformation of the urinary bladder; 2) the spleen fails to transport and transform water;
3) the lung fails to regulate water passage; and/or
4) liver qi stagnation affects the urinary bladder.

